description.narrative: Follow-up assessments of 737 children, of the total 1,869 children disengaged in 2016 and 2017 from the non-state group MILF, found that none of them have re-associated with any armed group. 33 of 50 grave violations against children were verified, highlighting continued risks to children. To reduce their risk of association, child protection focused religious sermons reached over 9,305 personsand the introduction of U-report further empowered (5,000 approximately) adolescents and youth to voice their ideas/issues. The new partnership established with the Ministry of Social Welfare and Development will contribute to build and gradually strengthen child protection system in the BARMM. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:07/02/2020
